 rsquo\;s assassination. Unrequited yearning\, alcoholism\, and suppressed 
 desires abound in this 80-minute one-act play that finally examines the fo
 rgotten life and dreams of Mrs. Lincoln\, through the lens of an idiot (pl
 aywright Cole Escola).<br /><br />Declared &ldquo\;one of the best comedie
 s in years&rdquo\; by <em>The New York Times</em>\, <em>Oh\, Mary!</em> re
 ceived Tony Awards for Best Leading Actor in a Play (Cole Escola) and Best
  Direction of a Play (Sam Pinkleton)\, Drama League Awards for Outstanding
  Play and Outstanding Direction of a Play\, as well as a special citation 
 from the New York Drama Critics&rsquo\; Circle. It was named a finalist fo
 r the Pulitzer Prize for Drama.</p>
